ame":"Hawise","type":"FIRST","meanings":["This female name (which has been corrupted down to Avice and Avis) is from Hadewisa, formed from the German name Hedvig, same as Edwig, which Wachter translates 'propugnator felicitatis;' say, 'fortunate soldier.'"],"variants":[]}],"historicEvents":[{"id":1705187,"age":86,"year":"1215","julianDay":2164830,"title":"Magna Carta","description":"King John of England agreed to a charter of rights called the Magna Carta. The document was originally drafted by the Archbishop of Canterbury to establish peace between King John and a group of rebel barons. The Magna Carta was completed in 1215 and is now considered to be one of the greatest constitutional documents of all time.","url":"https://www.nationalarchives.gov.uk/education/medieval/magna-carta/","urlTitle":"National Archives - Magna Carta","jurisdictionLevel":2},{"id":1705188,"age":95,"year":"1224","julianDay":2168117,"title":"France Declares War on England","description":"France declared war on England as Louis VIII of France attacked Poitou and northern Gascony.","jurisdictionLevel":2}],"lifeSummary":"Hawise de Courcy was born in 1129, in Courtenay, Loiret, Centre, France as the daughter of William de Courcy and Matilda d'Avranches. She had at least 3 sons with Reinauld De Seigneur De Courtenay. She died in 1240, in Hungary, at the age of 111, and was buried in Ford Bridge, Herefordshire, England."},"et":{"1129–1240":"1129–1240","1150–1219":"1150–1219","1130–1194":"1130–1194","1173–1242":"1173–1242","1176–Male":"1176–Surnud","1183–1242":"1183–1242","1107–1162":"1107–1162","–1173":"–1173","1176":"1176","1242":"1242","27 September 1194":"27. september 1194","1240":"1240","1130":"1130","August 1209":"august 1209","1162":"1162","1173":"1173","1183":"1183","1194":"1194","1150":"1150","21 September 1173":"21. september 1173","1129":"1129","1107":"1107","1215":"1215","ABT 1176":"umbes 1176","1224":"1224","after 1173":"pärast 1173","before 1162":"enne 1162","1219":"1219","Ford, Hert